INSERT INTO `Background` VALUES ('553','Histachii','Racial','General','Arcana, Insight','Dragon Magazine 386','0','\r\n\r\n<!DOCTYPE HTML>\r\n<html>\r\n<head id=\"Head1\"><title>\r\nHistachii\r\n</title><meta http-equiv=\"X-UA-Compatible\" content=\"IE=EmulateIE7\" /><link href=\"styles/detail.css\" media=\"screen\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" /><link href=\"styles/print.css\" media=\"print\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" /><link href=\"styles/mobile.css\" media=\"handheld\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" />\r\n    \r\n    \r\n    \r\n\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n    <form name=\"form1\" method=\"post\" action=\"display.php?page=background&amp;id=553\" id=\"form1\">\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n    <div id=\"detail\">\r\n\r\n<h1   class=\"player\">Histachii</h1><p class=\"flavortext\"><b>Type: </b>Racial<br/><b>Campaign Setting: </b>General<br/><b>Prerequisite: </b>Human<br/></p>Your golden eyes set you apart from your kin for they marked you as histachii, touched by Merrshaulk. Your kin believed you had insights into the demon’s mind and could protect them from his dreaded bite. How did your heritage shape your destiny as an adventurer? Were your villagers’ superstitions correct? Did you have visions or insights? What were they?<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<i>Associated Skills: </i>Arcana, Insight<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<i>Associated Languages: </i>Draconic<br/><p class=\"publishedIn\">Published in <a href=\"http://anonym.to/?http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=dnd/drtoc/386\" target=\"_new\">Dragon Magazine 386</a>, page(s) 7.</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    </form>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>\r\n\r\n<script type=\"text/javascript\">\r\n    if (document.all) {\r\n        if (document.documentMode != 9) {\r\n            var ar = document.getElementsByTagName(\'span\');\r\n            for (var i = 0; i < ar.length; i++ ) {\r\n                var c = ar[i].attributes[\'class\'].value;\r\n                if (c == \'milevel\')\r\n                    ar[i].style.top = \"-24px\";\r\n                else if (c == \'miright\')\r\n                    ar[i].style.top = \"-18px\";\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n</script>\r\n');
INSERT INTO `Background` VALUES ('554','Wayfinder','Racial','General','Endurance, Nature','Dragon Magazine 386','0','\r\n\r\n<!DOCTYPE HTML>\r\n<html>\r\n<head id=\"Head1\"><title>\r\nWayfinder\r\n</title><meta http-equiv=\"X-UA-Compatible\" content=\"IE=EmulateIE7\" /><link href=\"styles/detail.css\" media=\"screen\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" /><link href=\"styles/print.css\" media=\"print\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" /><link href=\"styles/mobile.css\" media=\"handheld\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" />\r\n    \r\n    \r\n    \r\n\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n    <form name=\"form1\" method=\"post\" action=\"display.php?page=background&amp;id=554\" id=\"form1\">\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n    <div id=\"detail\">\r\n\r\n<h1   class=\"player\">Wayfinder</h1><p class=\"flavortext\"><b>Type: </b>Racial<br/><b>Campaign Setting: </b>General<br/><b>Prerequisite: </b>Human<br/></p>No one knows the swamp’s dangers better than you do, because it was your task to bring news to the neighboring communities and to gather information to bring back to the elders. Your travels revealed much about the swamp’s secrets, helping you find secret paths none knew about. Why did you leave your village? Did you become lost? Was your village destroyed while you were away? Are you, perhaps, an envoy to the larger world?<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<i>Associated Skills: </i>Endurance, Nature<br/><p class=\"publishedIn\">Published in <a href=\"http://anonym.to/?http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=dnd/drtoc/386\" target=\"_new\">Dragon Magazine 386</a>, page(s) 7.</p>\r\n    </div>\r\n    </form>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>\r\n\r\n<script type=\"text/javascript\">\r\n    if (document.all) {\r\n        if (document.documentMode != 9) {\r\n            var ar = document.getElementsByTagName(\'span\');\r\n            for (var i = 0; i < ar.length; i++ ) {\r\n                var c = ar[i].attributes[\'class\'].value;\r\n                if (c == \'milevel\')\r\n               